[SN]TITLE[SN]
ICYMI: Ashley Madison hacked and Iniesta's Instagram woe

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
In Case You Missed It: a round-up of interesting technology-related links shared over the weekend.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Online Cheating Site AshleyMadison Hacked (Krebs on Security)
Security journalist/researcher Brian Krebs reports that dating site Ashley Madison, which seeks to set up extra-marital affairs, has been hacked.
The Snapchat Elections Begin With Bernie, Hillary and Jeb (Recode)
US Presidential hopefuls are turning to Snapchat in an attempt to connect with potential voters - and pulling that "parents on Skype not sure if it's on" face as they go.
UCLA Health System reports patient data breach; 4.5 million may be affected (LA Times)
There's a sense of "here we go again" with this, but that only highlights how worrying it is. A huge, possibly 4.5 million in total, breach of medical data.
How Instagram closed my account and gave it to a football celebrity (Medium)
Football fans will know Andres Iniesta well - he scored the goal that won the World Cup for Spain in 2010. But you may be less familar with Andres Iniesta, a bloke who absolutely didn't score the goal that won the World Cup for Spain in 2010.
